#7301
THE NEW YORK STOCK EXCHANGE~

You are in a room filled with various machines and computers, they look like
some sort of stock price quotation devices.  The floor here is covered with
all kinds of papers, some say BUY some say SELL on it.  This place is a real
mess. It looks like a thousand people have trampled these floors for the 
entire day.  As you look further, you notice a figure slumped over in the dark
corner. As you walk closer, you notice he is in a fetal position.  He shivers
and shakes as you approach him.  You ask him his name.  He answers :
I am Gordon Gekko, stock broker extrodinare, and this is what i look like
after a day at the office.

As you peer around, you see one of the most used exits here at the exchange.
The WINDOW.  You feel the urge to jump out of it.  It's only a 150 foot drop...
straight down to the Temple of Midgaard.
